<paragraph id="40973DCB8021952E70E887E192296AA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
3.2.5. 
<taxonomicName id="959D91D2F8921F6042DC9CFD5AEA80A6" LSID="B6342569-70FB-544C-8EE8-8B135104B8D9" authority="Hebard, 1916" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Symploce Hebard, 1916</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4599C6DE18DC93B3BA4BAEC64A66D59" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="notes">
<paragraph id="79DBD79050F4D2AB33CA51CF6E19830E" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9EE33499B920227AB4DE86A175AE2C93" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
In this genus, with the type species 
<taxonomicName id="DFC92507307021D6EEA378688BB0DA10" family="Blaberoidea" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. hebardi" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="species" species="hebardi">
<emphasis id="41FA5D2B34DE07D8795C02C0D1D64D5A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">S. hebardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Princis, 1969 (not included in our analyses), we establish two new species mainly according to the morphological characters. In addition, inferred from our phylogenetic analyses (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="500C7591C24C06EB49CC95DCCE17F38C" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on three mitochondrial genes 12 S rRNA, 16 S rRNA, COII and two nuclear genes 28 S rRNA, histone H 3. The topologies yielded by Bayesian inference (BI) are almost identical with ML tree (see supplementary material Fig. S 1). Branch labels provide bootstrap support (bs) of nodes in ML and posterior probability (pp) (%) of nodes in BI; (*) indicates the branch label of the corresponding analysis is 100 or 1.0, respectively; (-) means the node is absent for the given analysis." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690401" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">1</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="310B5AF3D645E95D1F2ED574CC7CDDD4" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce maxima" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis id="5A1478DA10874EAB9D5380BE5D308A36" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li, Liu, Qiu and Yue is grouped together with other 
<taxonomicName id="EEB75F4C0CEFC45723F46D8D1B22173F" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="556F7411FE1CF9C419A7996610D57B52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species; thus, we propose one new combination.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
